00:39:34.450 --> 00:39:40.158
Olivia Morris. who officially would never go out
with me. is dead. So is Jenny Randall and Marnie Cooper.

420
00:39:40.492 --> 00:39:44.083
Our local legacy. the Stab movies. is coming to life.

421
00:39:44.283 --> 00:39:50.242
- Excuse me. are you recording with that thing?
- My video blog upload. He's webcasting right now.

422
00:39:50.442 --> 00:39:54.658
- Mind turning it off? A little old school. off the record?
- Can't. Owe it to my audience.

423
00:39:54.858 --> 00:39:57.408
- Turn the fucking thing off.
- Ok...

424
00:39:59.325 --> 00:40:03.417
- So. you two are the boys who run the
movie club at Woodsboro High. huh?

425
00:40:03.617 --> 00:40:07.783
- Oh. Charlie rents it. I'm just VP. in case he takes a bullet.
- It's called Cinema Club.

426
00:40:08.408 --> 00:40:14.367
- So you must have a very unique insight into the movie buffs at your school?
- Maybe.

427
00:40:15.242 --> 00:40:18.542
What if we could catch the killer. by working together?

428
00:40:18.742 --> 00:40:24.158
Two generations of cutting edge journalists
intertwining our passions for media.

429
00:40:25.367 --> 00:40:28.033
- What would you say?
- I love you?

430
00:40:28.825 --> 00:40:36.325
Very good. Now. you give me your expertise on the gore geek
scene at Woodsboro High and maybe I give you something in return

431
00:40:36.783 --> 00:40:44.658
- Say. a celebrity visit to your Cinema Club...by me?
- What about Sidney?

432
00:40:45.992 --> 00:40:48.867
- What about Sidney?
- Hey. you know her. right? I am you're friends with her?

433
00:40:50.075 --> 00:40:56.075
No offense but. that'd be a big deal for some of the club.
A visit from Sidney Prescott. I mean. she's the star.

434
00:40:56.275 --> 00:41:00.158
Uh. yes she's Daniel Radcliffe to my J.K. Rowling.

435
00:41:00.358 --> 00:41:04.242
- When was the bookshelf in the box office?
- Never.

436
00:41:08.117 --> 00:41:12.325
- There's no broken bones. I think you'll be
fine. Maybe just take a couple weeks off.

437
00:41:15.742 --> 00:41:22.658
So. Sidney...Uh. ouh. Anyway. long story short
. Random wants to lock you into 3 more books. now.

438
00:41:22.992 --> 00:41:26.417
See the blank line in your contract? You can name your phrase.

439
00:41:26.617 --> 00:41:29.917
And as soon as you re clear in this investigation.
we re on the next plane to New York.

440
00:41:30.117 --> 00:41:35.408
- I booked Today. The View. Nancy Grace. MTV News.
- Excuse me. can I...can I ask you a question?

441
00:41:36.325 --> 00:41:40.958
- Did you read my book?
- Thought I'd wait for the movie.

442
00:41:41.158 --> 00:41:52.783
- Book tour is over.
- Sidney. Accept your situation. You re a victim. for life. So. embrace it. use it.

443
00:41:53.658 --> 00:41:57.958
I know you care about your readers. All those little
down-trodden fucks that just need a light at the end of their

444
00:41:58.158 --> 00:42:04.325
tunnels so they don't jump off a bridge. And a lucky break
like this? I am talking a 100 percent increase in sales. minimum.

445
00:42:04.525 --> 00:42:09.575
That's maybe a million more people getting your
message and you get a ton more checks. Win-win.

446
00:42:11.908 --> 00:42:14.492
- I won't be needing you anymore.
- Sidney!

447
00:42:14.692 --> 00:42:16.617
- You re fired.
- Fired?

448
00:42:16.817 --> 00:42:19.700
- Fired!
- Fine.

449
00:42:42.242 --> 00:42:44.200
"What do you think about my book. Rebecca?"

450
00:42:57.700 --> 00:43:02.242
The problem of Sidney is she never gets laid.
Or even a little shit faced once in a while.

451
00:43:03.658 --> 00:43:07.117
She'll call me at 9 to apologize. Just watch.

452
00:43:14.283 --> 00:43:21.075
She'll come around. Gotta just give her
time. Sidney will come...around.

453
00:43:33.158 --> 00:43:35.992
<i>- This is Rebecca.
- Sidney Prescott. please.</i>

454
00:43:36.450 --> 00:43:39.825
I am handling Ms Prescott's calls and appearances.
May I take a message?

455
00:43:40.025 --> 00:43:48.917
<i>You are the message. Are you writing this down?
- Yes. I am.</i>

456
00:43:49.117 --> 00:43:53.992
But. it's kinda hard to hear you. I'm in a hospital.
with Sidney. If you can just hang on one second.

457
00:43:54.575 --> 00:43:57.992
<i>I've got time. It's you that doesn't.</i>

458
00:44:05.742 --> 00:44:09.325
<i>You know. Rebecca. it doesn't
sound to me like you re in the hospital.</i>

459
00:44:09.825 --> 00:44:16.533
<i>Sounds like you re in a parking garage.
A dark and deserted parking garage.</i>

460
00:44:18.117 --> 00:44:23.242
<i>But if you wanna be in the hospital. I'd be
happy to put you there. In the morgue!</i>

461
00:45:10.117 --> 00:45:13.700
Help! Help! Save me!

462
00:45:29.325 --> 00:45:32.158
Cut and run. you fucking bastard.

463
00:46:40.825 --> 00:46:47.325
This is an ongoing investigation.
But rest assured. we re pursuing a number of leads.

464
00:46:47.525 --> 00:46:49.658
- Sheriff
- The less I say about that. the better.

465
00:46:50.242 --> 00:46:52.533
So. I'm taking questions.

466
00:46:53.533 --> 00:46:55.450
- Dewey!
- Gale?

467
00:46:55.700 --> 00:47:01.158
Any comment on the fact that these killings seem to
resemble the pattern of the original Woodsboro murders?

468
00:47:01.450 --> 00:47:03.325
Hun? Later!

469
00:47:04.283 --> 00:47:05.367
<i>What was that. Sheriff?</i>

470
00:47:05.617 --> 00:47:09.375
As I was saying...my officers are hard at work.

471
00:47:09.575 --> 00:47:16.242
We just want the community to know that we re very
close to bringing this whole situation under control.

472
00:47:23.492 --> 00:47:26.371
Hey. someone! Get up to the top
of the structure! Go! Go!

473
00:47:26.571 --> 00:47:29.450
<i>- Everyone back! Stay back!
- Back. nobody move!</i>

474
00:47:29.650 --> 00:47:31.575
Jenkins. I want a man on this stairwell.

475
00:47:34.033 --> 00:47:36.575
<i>- You see anybody?
- Nobody out there.</i>

476
00:47:36.992 --> 00:47:38.658
There's nobody out there. Sheriff!

477
00:47:40.450 --> 00:47:44.667
- It's all under control huh. Sheriff?
- But what am I supposed to say?

478
00:47:44.867 --> 00:47:49.367
Listen. I may not be wearing a uniform.
but I happen to have a lead and you don't.

479
00:47:51.033 --> 00:47:53.367
So let me know when you re back on Team Gale.

480
00:47:55.450 --> 00:47:56.908
Move back. I am the Sheriff.

481
00:48:07.408 --> 00:48:12.792
Ok. Cinema Club. we re not in session.
Welcome. I'll tell you a little bit about ourselves.

482
00:48:12.992 --> 00:48:19.950
We re a sanctioned after school activity. one
rung below the Glee club. two above Nintendo Wii Fit

483
00:48:20.150 --> 00:48:25.575
and let me just say to our guest
. Sidney Prescott. it's an honor.

484
00:48:29.075 --> 00:48:33.158
Beyond Jamie Lee Curtis. forget Linda Blair.
I mean. this is the ultimate.

485
00:48:33.658 --> 00:48:40.450
Thanks. I-I guess. This. uhm...you film your entire
High School experience and what. post it on the net?

486
00:48:40.650 --> 00:48:44.292
- Everybody will be doing it someday. Sid.
- It's kind of the one component the killer is missing.

487
00:48:44.492 --> 00:48:51.492
- Wait. what do you mean?
- Well. if you wanna be the new "new version". the killer should be filming the murders.

488
00:48:51.692 --> 00:48:55.929
That's like the natural next step in the psycho
slasher innovation. I mean you film em all real time

489
00:48:56.129 --> 00:49:00.367
- and then before you get caught. you upload em into cyberspace.
- Making your art as immortal as you.

490
00:49:01.408 --> 00:49:02.908
- Not to implicate him...
- Not to implicate me...

491
00:49:03.242 --> 00:49:08.950
- So who do you think is behind the murders?
- Well. it's a Stab fanatic. clearly.

492
00:49:09.283 --> 00:49:12.992
Working on less of a Screquel and more of a Screamake.
- Copyrighted terms. by the way.

493
00:49:13.192 --> 00:49:16.658
Cos all there are now are remakes.
Only horror the studios green-light.

494
00:49:16.950 --> 00:49:21.617
I mean. there are still rules. but the rules have changed.
The unexpected is the new cliché.

495
00:49:21.817 --> 00:49:24.250
Yeah. you gotta have an opening sequence
that blows the doors off

496
00:49:24.450 --> 00:49:28.375
done with some flashy music video direction.
And the kills gotta be way more extreme.

497
00:49:28.575 --> 00:49:33.683
Modern audiences got savvy to the rules of the originals.
so the reversals become the new standard.

498
00:49:33.883 --> 00:49:38.992
In fact. the only surefire way to survive a modern
horror movie. you pretty much have to be gay.

499
00:49:41.950 --> 00:49:48.325
So. why are you so sure that the killer is working by the rules of a horror remake?
- Well. the original Stab structure is pretty apparent.

500
00:49:48.525 --> 00:49:53.367
- Two kids killed in a house while their parents are away.
- And then the school's "hot chick" savaged beyond recognition.

501
00:49:53.567 --> 00:49:55.867
- We all know where it goes from there...
- A party.

502
00:49:56.533 --> 00:50:03.408
- Exactly. A party. Guaranteed third act main cast blood bath.
- Fingers crossed on some nudity for a change.

503
00:50:05.742 --> 00:50:10.533
- Ok. do you know of a party that's happening tonight?
- Well. there's Stab- a- thon.

504
00:50:11.783 --> 00:50:17.458
- Stab- a- thon?
- Uh. It's a movie marathon. All 7 Stabs back to back. We do it every year.

505
00:50:17.658 --> 00:50:24.742
- Is tonight? There's a killer out there patterning his murders after the original movie.
- I know. it's pretty wild.

506
00:50:24.942 --> 00:50:26.033
We have to call it off.

507
00:50:26.408 --> 00:50:31.367
- Uhm. ok. I mean. it's Friday. I am sure we re not
the only party that's going on at Woodsboro.

508
00:50:31.567 --> 00:50:35.625
- But where is this circle-jerk gonna take place?
- So. let's ready for this Q&A.

509
00:50:35.825 --> 00:50:41.742
- No. no. I really want the location.
- You know. it's kind of an underground thing. Email invites. Pretty secret.

510
00:50:42.783 --> 00:50:48.950
What. you re not gonna tell me? Really?
We re working together. Remember?

511
00:50:50.325 --> 00:50:53.450
- So you re ready for the Q&A?
- Fuck you. Let's go.

512
00:50:57.783 --> 00:50:58.992
That was awesome.

513
00:50:59.617 --> 00:51:02.408
- Nobody comes to the house unless we say so.
- Got it.

514
00:51:02.608 --> 00:51:04.492
I feel like I'm under house arrest.

515
00:51:19.867 --> 00:51:27.492
You know when people say "I know how you feel". but
you know they re just saying that because they really have no

516
00:51:27.692 --> 00:51:33.825
freaking idea how you feel? I know how you feel.

517
00:51:37.742 --> 00:51:40.242
I am so sorry about Olivia.

518
00:51:45.200 --> 00:51:47.033
I am sorry about your publicist.

519
00:51:52.158 --> 00:51:58.992
How do you handle it. people staring at you all the time?
- People stare at me?

520
00:52:01.075 --> 00:52:06.242
I could never handle that kind of attention.
I just feel like it would take over your whole life.

521
00:52:09.075 --> 00:52:22.450
Uh. all I do is I...try not to think about me.
I have people I care about. I focus on them.

522
00:52:24.325 --> 00:52:27.492
And the rest. uhm. it works out.

523
00:52:29.783 --> 00:52:35.742
You saved my life last night. I mean. I know
we re family but... you heard a thing on me.

524
00:52:37.075 --> 00:52:42.117
Makes me wonder. you know.
if I'd be brave enough to do the same thing.

525
00:52:44.117 --> 00:52:46.700
I really hope you never have to find that out.

526
00:52:50.325 --> 00:52:53.117
Oh. if you need me. you know where to find me.

527
00:52:53.617 --> 00:52:56.700
I'll be up in my cell. oh. I mean. my room.

528
00:53:21.117 --> 00:53:26.867
Our rooms are boarded up. That's the
view from my cell. It's really weird.

529
00:53:27.450 --> 00:53:30.908
I think Olivia would understand. ok?
She'd want me to be around other people.

530
00:53:31.783 --> 00:53:36.158
Holy shit. Even if I did just crash land on planet dork.

531
00:53:37.700 --> 00:53:40.500
Speaking of which. Trevor's here.
- Hey. Kirby.

532
00:53:40.700 --> 00:53:45.450
- What is he doing there? That is so not his scene.
- I have no idea. maybe he thought you would be here.

533
00:53:45.742 --> 00:53:50.392
Yeah. fat chance. After what happened last night?
I mean. my mum is just completely freaked out.

534
00:53:50.592 --> 00:53:55.242
- It's not prim.
- Alright. you go do your good girl thing and I'll drink for the both of us.

535
00:53:55.442 --> 00:53:58.617
- I will keep you posted.
- Alright. be safe.

536
00:54:42.825 --> 00:54:47.792
Stab-a-thon!
Stab-a-thon!

537
00:54:47.992 --> 00:54:51.992
- Thank you! Thank you. Gracias. Gracias.
- Shhhh.

538
00:54:53.325 --> 00:54:56.408
Cinema Club thanks you for coming up for our third annual Stab-a-thon.

539
00:54:56.608 --> 00:54:58.375
Thank you. number-3-thon. We thank you in rows.

540
00:54:58.575 --> 00:55:02.450
- Are you ready to drink every time someone can't get a cellphone signal?
- Yeah!

541
00:55:02.742 --> 00:55:08.617
- Are you ready to drink every time someone shuts the refrigerator
door and. oh my God. there's the harmless character right behind it?

542
00:55:08.817 --> 00:55:09.875
Yeah!

543
00:55:10.075 --> 00:55:14.075
- Are you ready to drink every time somebody screams the word...
- No!

544
00:55:14.275 --> 00:55:17.200
Let's get the Stab-athon started!

545
00:55:33.200 --> 00:55:34.617
<i>Ghostface!</i>

546
00:55:35.658 --> 00:55:36.992
<i>Get out in 5!</i>

547
00:55:38.075 --> 00:55:39.408
<i>Move your ass!</i>

548
00:55:39.992 --> 00:55:41.033
Screw you!

549
00:56:17.242 --> 00:56:18.242
Yes!

550
00:56:25.242 --> 00:56:27.367
Uh. Yeah. Back on my game.

551
00:56:29.283 --> 00:56:32.533
Perfect. New work in progress. chapter 1.

552
00:56:32.867 --> 00:56:39.575
When I moved to Woodsboro. I never in a million
years dreamed that I would again play the critical role...

553
00:56:39.775 --> 00:56:42.158
...in solving another series of these...

554
00:56:50.825 --> 00:56:51.950
What the hell?

555
00:57:15.492 --> 00:57:19.117
- Gale. where are you?
- I followed the kids to the Stab-a-thon.

556
00:57:19.367 --> 00:57:26.117
There's an old abandoned farm on 4th Dylan Road.
Listen. I-I got it under surveillance. but I think the killer is about to make his move.

557
00:57:26.658 --> 00:57:32.575
- What makes you so sure?
- You do a remake to outdo the original. that's what the kids said.

558
00:57:32.775 --> 00:57:36.950
This party is all about the Stab movies.
Come on. how meta can you get?

559
00:57:37.450 --> 00:57:41.075
- How "what the.." can you get?
- I dunno. I heard em say it.

560
00:57:41.492 --> 00:57:47.825
- Dewey. listen to me. you have to get out here.
Come on. you catch the killer. I get the story. It's a win-win.

561
00:57:48.025 --> 00:57:52.658
- Well. I thought you were going rogue. Gale.
- Oh come..are you serious? C'mon!

562
00:57:53.742 --> 00:57:59.700
- Forget it. Thanks for having faith in me! I gotta fix my equipment.
- Gale!

563
00:58:02.492 --> 00:58:03.492
Shit.

564
00:58:18.617 --> 00:58:25.575
Bravo. well...very well done. very. I'm very impressed.
Kind of. Kinda impressed. Not Really.

565
00:58:25.950 --> 00:58:27.583
- That'll do.
- Yeah? - Yeah.

566
00:58:27.783 --> 00:58:30.117
- Yeah. she wants you.
- Yeah. Yeah.

567
00:58:32.950 --> 00:58:35.533
<i>Nooooooo!</i>

568
00:58:37.950 --> 00:58:38.783
<i>Ghostface...</i>

569
00:58:47.908 --> 00:58:50.242
<i>- Hello?
- Hello.</i>

570
00:58:51.242 --> 00:58:55.242
<i>- Who is this?
- Were you expecting somebody now?</i>

571
00:59:02.575 --> 00:59:06.075
<i>You know. I don't even know you...
- ...and I dislike you already.</i>

572
00:59:06.367 --> 00:59:10.242
- Hicks. how far are you from 4th Dylan Road?
- 5 minutes at the most. Sir.

573
00:59:10.442 --> 00:59:10.992
Well. step on it.

574
00:59:13.408 --> 00:59:14.658
<i>Look out your window.</i>

575
01:00:00.075 --> 01:00:02.408
Gale! Gale. behind you!

576
01:00:14.700 --> 01:00:15.242
No!

577
01:00:19.242 --> 01:00:20.075
Gale!

578
01:00:35.617 --> 01:00:36.450
Freeze!

579
01:00:50.242 --> 01:00:51.825
Get out of the way. you morons!

580
01:00:57.367 --> 01:00:58.242
Dammit.

581
01:01:01.783 --> 01:01:04.750
- Ok. put pressure on that.
- Did you catch him?

582
01:01:04.950 --> 01:01:10.200
- No. hopefully your cameras got something.
- They weren't the only ones. Dewey.

583
01:01:10.400 --> 01:01:13.492
- What?
- There's a webcam... set back there.

584
01:01:13.692 --> 01:01:16.283
- He was watching me.
- A webcam?

585
01:01:16.742 --> 01:01:19.325
- He's recording the murders.
- What?

586
01:01:19.825 --> 01:01:23.200
This time... he's making the movie.

587
01:01:27.783 --> 01:01:31.992
This Sidney Prescott detail man. I don't like it.

588
01:01:32.742 --> 01:01:34.825
The cops scouting the house. they always get it.

589
01:01:36.200 --> 01:01:38.742
What are you talking about?
- It's a movie cop rule.

590
01:01:39.158 --> 01:01:44.783
Sucks to be a cop in a movie. Unless you re Bruce Willis.
- Not all cops die in movies.

591
01:01:45.408 --> 01:01:48.950
No. but if it's your last day before retirement you do.

592
01:01:49.742 --> 01:01:52.533
If you re a rookie. some with a wife
who's pregnant. you do.

593
01:01:54.075 --> 01:01:58.158
Or if your partner is better looking than you.
you do. and by the way. I win that one.

594
01:02:00.367 --> 01:02:03.158
You know what. I'll take the next perimeter. I'll be right back.

595
01:02:05.533 --> 01:02:06.125
Shit.

596
01:02:06.325 --> 01:02:11.208
- I know this one. you re not supposed to say that. are you?
- Eh. new decade. new rules.

597
01:02:11.408 --> 01:02:17.533
You know. these days. you might come back. find me
dead. Eyes gouged out. tongue sticking out. Could go either way.

598
01:02:17.733 --> 01:02:21.242
- I gotta learn this shit.
- Eh. I'll take this one.

599
01:02:23.658 --> 01:02:28.867
- Hey. Hoss. Be careful.
- I am always careful.

600
01:02:32.783 --> 01:02:34.450
Dead man walking.

601
01:03:24.658 --> 01:03:32.075
- Perkins. was there a window open on your
last perimeter check? Perkins. come in. Over.

602
01:04:03.075 --> 01:04:03.575
Anthony?

603
01:04:05.867 --> 01:04:06.367
Perkins?

604
01:04:12.033 --> 01:04:15.908
- Dammit.
- You should have seen the look on your face. rookie.

605
01:04:18.242 --> 01:04:20.242
Hoss! What the fuck!

606
01:04:22.367 --> 01:04:23.408
Holy shit...

607
01:04:34.158 --> 01:04:34.950
Hoss!

608
01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:52.167
Fuck Bruce Willis!

609
01:05:21.375 --> 01:05:26.792
- Sorry. The wind chimes were over here.
- It was me. I was trying to fix em. sorry.

610
01:05:28.667 --> 01:05:31.708
- I am just back the store.
- Were you shopping?

611
01:05:32.042 --> 01:05:36.167
A stress buster. I got one more bag
in the car. I'll be right back.

612
01:06:02.458 --> 01:06:03.875
Jill. you re gonna get that?

613
01:06:08.292 --> 01:06:11.342
<i>- Roberts residence.
- You re a survivor. aren't you. Sidney?</i>

614
01:06:11.542 --> 01:06:16.917
<i>Your one and only skill: You survive.
Well. I have one question for you.</i>

615
01:06:17.542 --> 01:06:22.125
<i>What good did to be a survivor in this little drama if everyone close to you is dead?</i>

616
01:06:22.625 --> 01:06:25.425
<i>- Who are you?
- Turn on the TV to channel 6.</i>

617
01:06:25.625 --> 01:06:29.083
<i>- Who the fuck are you?
- Turn it on. Watch the teaser.</i>

618
01:06:30.958 --> 01:06:36.758
<i>...But it nearly turned deadly tonight. with the latest
victim of this attack being the wife of the Woodsboro Sheriff...</i>

619
01:06:36.958 --> 01:06:44.167
<i>...Gale Riley. AKA Gale Weathers. who's in serious condition
tonight after being stabbed. Her assailant then disappeared...</i>

