I was so believable today. wasn't I? I mean. I told so many lies.
I actually started to believe them. I really think that I was born for this.

818
01:28:23.458 --> 01:28:29.967
- How could you do this?
- Do you know what it was like growing up in this family?

819
01:28:30.217 --> 01:28:38.300
Related to you? I mean. all I ever heard was:
Sidney this and Sidney that. and Sidney. Sidney. Sidney.

820
01:28:38.758 --> 01:28:46.342
- You were always so fucking special! Well. now I am the special one.
- You'll slip. they always do.

821
01:28:47.758 --> 01:29:02.675
- Come on. Charlie. Let's go on with this. You have to be strong and hold still. Ok?
- Yeah. yeah. old school. like Billy and Stu. Come on. baby. get it up. Come on.

822
01:29:03.758 --> 01:29:06.300
Shoulder me. shoulder me. shoulder me. Get it up!

823
01:29:12.675 --> 01:29:14.142
Not the way we rehearsed it.

824
01:29:14.342 --> 01:29:17.717
You said it. Charlie: Billy and Stu. Trevor and you.

825
01:29:19.050 --> 01:29:30.925
What the media really loves. baby. is a sole survivor. Just ask you
know who. Trevor was your partner and you. you were the idea man.

826
01:29:41.008 --> 01:29:51.050
- Even your friends?
- My friends? What world are you living in? I don't need friends. I need fans.

827
01:29:51.800 --> 01:29:59.508
Don't you get it?! This has never been
about killing you. It's about...becoming you.

828
01:30:00.175 --> 01:30:05.967
I mean. for fuck's sake. my own mother had to die.
no great loss there. so I could stay true to the original.

829
01:30:06.550 --> 01:30:15.050
It's sick. right? Well sick is the new sane.
You had your 15 minutes. no I want mine!

830
01:30:16.050 --> 01:30:25.846
I mean. what am I supposed to do? Go to college. grad school. work?
Look around. we all live in public now. we re all on the Internet.

831
01:30:26.046 --> 01:30:35.842
How do you think people become famous anymore? You don't have
to achieve anything. You just gotta have fucked up shit happen to you.

832
01:30:36.758 --> 01:30:45.967
So. you do have to die Sid. Those are the rules. New movie. new
franchise. There's only room for one lead and. let's face it.

833
01:30:46.167 --> 01:30:48.800
your ingenue days. they are over.

834
01:30:55.425 --> 01:30:57.425
Don't tell me you didn't know this day would come.

835
01:32:17.633 --> 01:32:19.717
Oh. fuck!

836
01:33:40.383 --> 01:33:41.633
Come on! Let's move in!

837
01:33:52.050 --> 01:33:54.467
- Check the rooms. both sides and upstairs.
- Yes Ma'm.

838
01:34:12.425 --> 01:34:30.842
Jill can you give us a description...Over
here...Jill...Jill. how does it feel to be a hero?..

839
01:34:42.300 --> 01:34:48.767
- Jill. You made it. That's all that matters.
- True. Charlie and Trev tried to kill me.

840
01:34:48.967 --> 01:34:57.758
And I heard they killed my mom. And Robbie and Kirby too.
- Shhh. Just lay back. Try to rest.

841
01:34:59.842 --> 01:35:04.342
- Is-is your wife...
- She's gonna be fine. She's tough.

842
01:35:07.300 --> 01:35:15.675
If I ever write a book one day I'd. I'd want her to write it with me.
It'd be a good team with our matching wounds and all.

843
01:35:18.842 --> 01:35:30.300
We're survivors now. I just wish Sidney was too.
- Jill. they re not sure yet. It's still touch and go.

844
01:35:31.342 --> 01:35:35.883
But she's in ICU (intensive care unit) and
they think Sidney just might make it.

845
01:35:37.342 --> 01:35:46.008
What? I mean. I saw Trevor kill her.
- Look. we don't know yet. But she's hanging on.

846
01:35:49.258 --> 01:35:58.258
I-I-I wanna se her.
- She's not awake yet. And. she may not remember anything. You'll have to help her with that.

847
01:35:59.717 --> 01:36:02.842
All in time. Just get some rest now. ok?

848
01:36:51.842 --> 01:36:56.725
- She gonna be ok?
- Yeah. she's a strong kid.

849
01:36:56.925 --> 01:37:05.717
- She's gonna have to be.
- She asked if you were ok. She thinks you guys should write a book together.

850
01:37:05.917 --> 01:37:09.508
- With your matching wounds.
- Why. she was stabbed in the shoulder?

851
01:37:13.842 --> 01:37:21.675
- How did she know I was too?
- Shit!

852
01:37:28.425 --> 01:37:37.758
You just won't die. will ya? Who are you.
Michael fucking Mayers? Yeah. I don't think so.

853
01:37:43.133 --> 01:37:44.800
Fucking die already!

854
01:38:08.425 --> 01:38:09.967
How are those stitches?

855
01:38:15.217 --> 01:38:16.092
<i>Sidney!</i>

856
01:38:20.508 --> 01:38:24.217
- Hicks. get to the Sidney Prescott's room and call for backup!
- Be right up. Sir.

857
01:38:32.758 --> 01:38:36.217
- Sid? Sid.
- Dewey!

858
01:38:55.133 --> 01:39:01.550
Is this how it's gonna be. Sid? The ending of the movie was
supposed to be at the house. I mean. this is just...silly.

859
01:39:02.092 --> 01:39:07.300
Consider this an alternate ending. You're not gonna get out of this. Jill.

860
01:39:07.500 --> 01:39:08.717
- Of course I will.
- Dewey?

861
01:39:10.717 --> 01:39:11.383
Sid...

862
01:39:12.592 --> 01:39:19.175
- Easy..Wait. wait. What about the book?
- Looks like I'll just have to write it myself.

863
01:39:21.425 --> 01:39:22.467
Goddammit!

864
01:39:24.758 --> 01:39:27.758
Don't even think about shooting or I'll blow Dewey's head off.

865
01:39:28.675 --> 01:39:32.717
- What. you think I won't do it? Give me your gun!
- Do it.

866
01:39:42.925 --> 01:39:47.300
You just had to be the hero. huh? Give me your gun.

867
01:39:50.092 --> 01:39:54.467
What are you. deaf? Give me...your gun.

868
01:40:02.133 --> 01:40:08.925
- And get up. And keep your hands over your head.
- Don't do anything stupi...

869
01:40:10.800 --> 01:40:12.842
Don't fucking tell me what to do.

870
01:40:13.550 --> 01:40:16.758
- Oh. God...
- Now. get up bitch.

871
01:40:17.342 --> 01:40:21.808
- Ok.
- Get up. Now!

872
01:40:22.008 --> 01:40:37.133
- Ok...
- Come on. Let's go. Get your skinny ass out here.

873
01:40:38.550 --> 01:40:43.925
- Ok...
- I'm gonna enjoy blowing your head off.

874
01:40:44.967 --> 01:40:52.925
Ok. but can I just have one final word?
- What? Please?

875
01:40:55.508 --> 01:40:56.300
- No...

876
01:40:59.508 --> 01:41:01.342
- Clear.
- Clear?

877
01:41:01.842 --> 01:41:02.467
Clear!

878
01:41:08.342 --> 01:41:12.217
You forgot the first rule of remakes. Jill: Don't fuck with the original.

879
01:41:17.092 --> 01:41:20.758
- Oh my God. Dewey.
- Uh. what hit me?

880
01:41:21.342 --> 01:41:26.008
Don't ask. You ok?

881
01:41:29.300 --> 01:41:34.592
- She was standing right behind?
- They always are.

882
01:41:47.550 --> 01:41:51.050
- Oh. God...
- Nice one.

883
01:41:53.050 --> 01:41:59.133
- Hicks. you're alive?
- Wear the vest. save your chest.

884
01:42:02.133 --> 01:42:07.842
I got two officers down. several injuries and a new suspect.

885
01:42:09.967 --> 01:42:12.300
We need a doctor. Goddammit!

886
01:42:13.175 --> 01:42:15.467
I dunno about you. but I feel a whole lot better.

887
01:42:19.425 --> 01:42:25.717
We're live at Woodsboro Community Hospital.
awaiting a first public statement from Jill Roberts. survivor.

888
01:42:25.917 --> 01:42:30.217
...a survivor of what is now being called "the Woodsboro Massacre reboot"...

889
01:42:30.417 --> 01:42:33.600
...Jill Roberts is her name. A name the whole world will now know...

890
01:42:33.800 --> 01:42:38.767
...who single-handedly put a stop to this 21st century Woodsboro killing spree...

891
01:42:38.967 --> 01:42:47.508
...Jill Roberts of Woodsboro. a girl who's lifted all our spirits tonight.
An American hero. right out of the movies.
